{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place all ingredients, except cornflour, into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, until combined.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and knead <nobr>30 sec\/<\/nobr>. Transfer dough onto a floured silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface. Divide dough into 8 equal portions (approx. 65 g each), shape into balls and cover with a kitchen towel.","Using a rolling pin dusted with cornflour, roll each ball into a circle (approx. 12-13 cm diameter). Dust dough with more cornflour to prevent sticking, if needed. Cover rolled dough with a kitchen towel to prevent it from drying out.","Place a non-stick frying pan over high heat; ensure pan is very hot before cooking flatbreads. Place 1 flatbread into pan and cook until bubbles begin to form and edges begin to lift (approx. 40 seconds). Turn flatbread over and cook for a further 40 seconds, pressing down gently using an egg flip. Transfer onto a plate and cover to keep warm. Repeat with remaining flatbread. Serve immediately (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["350 g gluten free flour mix (see Tips)","1 tbsp gluten free baking powder (see Tips)","1 ½ tsp salt","110 g water","50 g full cream milk","2 tbsp olive oil","gluten free cornflour, for dusting"]}],"id":"r124904","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-usxf_yyIBro\/XZWr3FTkAPI\/AAAAAAAAfuI\/H36l9x1E-9wDanyUfpy3oZJxJdDhGu3XwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_xg_2eWou6jXc6BBP.png","title":"Flatbreads","publishedAt":"2016-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1.7 g","fat":"5.1 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"39.8 g","calories":"896 kJ \/ 213 kcal"},"usefulItems":"kitchen towel, silicone bread mat, rolling pin, large non-stick frying pan, egg flip, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to the Gluten free flour mix and the Gluten free baking powder recipes on this recipe chip.","If not serving flatbread immediately, allow to cool then transfer into a sealable container and place into refrigerator for up to 3 days. To re-heat, sprinkle with water, wrap in aluminium foil and place into a moderate oven for 8-10 minutes (180°C), or until soft and warmed through.","Try serving flatbreads with Coconut fish curry and dahl as part of a complete meal. Please refer to the Coconut fish curry on this recipe chip. For the Tomato and lentil dahl recipe, please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em>."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","40m","8 portions"]}